\f5 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa225\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs30 \cf9 \cb3 \strokec9 Determined to fill in the gaps, the team started the study about 18 months ago. Dr. Philippe has extensive background in modeling fallout and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://moruroa-files.org/en/about"}}{\fldrslt \cf10 \ul \ulc10 \strokec10 was an author of a similar project in 2021}}\'a0that documented the effects from French nuclear tests.\cb1 \
\cb3 A breakthrough came in March, when Ms. Alzner and Megan Smith, another co-founder of shift7 and a former United States chief technology officer in the Obama administration, contacted the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration. There, Gilbert P. Compo, a senior research scientist at the University of Colorado and the NOAA Physical Sciences Laboratory, told the team that the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts had only a week earlier released historical data that charted weather patterns extending 30,000 feet or higher above Earth\'92s surface.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'93For the first time, we had the most accurate hourly reconstruction of the weather back to 1940, around the world,\'94 said Dr. Compo, who became a co-author on the study. \'93Every single event that puts something in the air, no matter what it is, can now be tracked, by the hour.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb3 Using the new data and software built by NOAA, Dr. Philippe then reanalyzed Trinity\'92s fallout. And while the study\'92s authors acknowledge limitations and uncertainties within their calculations, they maintain that \'93our estimates likely remain conservatively low.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa225\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs30 \cf9 \cb3 \strokec9 \'93It\'92s a very comprehensive, well-executed study,\'94 said M. V. Ramana, professor and Simons chair in disarmament, global and human security at the University of British Columbia, who was not involved in the study. Dr. Ramana was unsurprised by the study\'92s findings about Trinity. \'93I expected that the old estimates were understating what was actually deposited,\'94 he said.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb3 The results show that New Mexico was heavily affected by Trinity\'92s fallout. Computations by Dr. Philippe and his colleagues show the cloud\'92s trajectory primarily spreading up over northeast New Mexico and a part of the cloud circling to the south and west of ground zero over the next few days. The researchers wrote that there are \'93locations in New Mexico where radionuclide deposition reached levels on par with Nevada.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs32 \cf0 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa225\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs30 \cf9 \cb3 \strokec9 Trinity\'92s fallout, Dr. Philippe says, accounts for 87 percent of total deposition found across New Mexico, which also received deposition from Nevada\'92s aboveground tests. The study also found that Socorro County \'97 where the Trinity test took place \'97 has the fifth highest deposition per county of all counties in the United States.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb3 Trinity test \'93downwinders\'94 \'97 a term describing people who have lived near nuclear test sites and may have been exposed to deadly radioactive fallout \'97 have never been eligible for compensation under the 1990\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.justice.gov/civil/common/reca"}}{\fldrslt \cf10 \ul \ulc10 \strokec10 Radiation Exposure Compensation Act}}\'a0(RECA). It has provided over $2.5 billion in payments to nuclear workers in much of the Western U.S. and to downwinders who were located near the Nevada test site and may have developed cancer or other diseases as a result of radiation exposure.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa225\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs30 \cf9 \cb3 \strokec9 \'93Despite the Trinity test taking place in New Mexico, many New Mexicans were left out of the original RECA legislation and nobody has ever been able to explain why,\'94 said Senator Ben Ray Luj\'e1n, a New Mexico Democrat. He has helped lead efforts in Congress to expand and extend the legislation, currently due to sunset in 2024.\cb1 \
\cb3 Census data from 1940 shows that as many as 500,000 people were\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nationalgeographic.com/history/article/lawmakers-move-urgently-to-recognize-survivors-of-the-first-atomic-bomb-test"}}{\fldrslt \cf10 \ul \ulc10 \strokec10 living within a 150-mile radius}}\'a0of the test site. Some families lived as close as 12 miles away, according to the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.trinitydownwinders.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf10 \ul \ulc10 \strokec10 Tularosa Basin Downwinders Consortium}}. Yet no civilians were warned about the test ahead of time, and they weren't evacuated before or after the test.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'93This new information about the Trinity bomb is monumental and a long time coming,\'94 Tina Cordova, a co-founder of the consortium, said. \'93We\'92ve been waiting for an affirmation of the histories told by generations of people from Tularosa who witnessed the Trinity bomb and talked about how the ash fell from the sky for days afterward.\'94\cb1 \
\cb3 The study also documents significant deposition in Nevada, Utah, Wyoming, Colorado, Arizona and Idaho, as well as dozens of federally-recognized tribal lands, potentially strengthening the case for people seeking expanded compensation in those areas.\cb1 \
\cb3 Although Dr. Wellerstein said that he approaches such reanalyses of historical fallout with a certain amount of uncertainty, partly because of the age of the data, he said there is value in such studies by keeping nuclear history and its legacy in the public discourse.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb3 \'93The extent to which America nuked itself is not completely appreciated still, to this day, by most Americans, especially younger Americans,\'94 he said.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

